# Investigation Findings

## Email Sample 1

### Subject
URGENT: Verify Your Account

### Findings
- Fake sender domain detected
- Suspicious verification link
- Urgency-based language
- Generic greeting used

### Classification
Phishing

### Risk Level
High

---

## Email Sample 2

### Subject
Invoice Attached

### Findings
- Unknown attachment received
- Sender identity unclear
- No proper company signature

### Classification
Suspicious

### Risk Level
Medium

---

## Email Sample 3

### Subject
Monthly Newsletter

### Findings
- Trusted sender domain
- Valid HTTPS links
- No suspicious indicators

### Classification
Safe

### Risk Level
Low

---

# Overall Analysis

The majority of phishing attempts used:
- social engineering
- urgency
- fake domains
- credential harvesting links

These attacks target human behavior rather than system vulnerabilities.
